## App Boundaries (default ports)

- Admin Portal UI: `localhost:3000` (`admin-portal`)
- Admin APIs (protected): `localhost:3001` (`admin-portal-backend`)
- Public APIs (token protected): `localhost:3002` (`web-app-backend`)
- Center builder app: `localhost:3004` (`center-website`)
- Center runtime app: `localhost:3005` (`center-website/runtime`)

## Auth

- **Admin flows:** session/cookie ‚Üí `admin-portal-backend` (staff login via admin-portal).
- **Public consumers:** API access token ‚Üí `web-app-backend` (WP plugin, kiosk, runtime).
- API access tokens are generated in admin-portal by super admin.
- **Admin Portal ‚Üí Builder (Magic Link SSO**, Redis in `admin-portal-backend`):
  - Create: `POST /v1/center-website/magic-link/create` with `{ center_id, redirect_path? }`
    (default `redirect_path`: `/websites/:center_id`)
  - Consume: `POST /v1/public/center-website/magic-link/consume` (builder sets session
    cookie, redirects to `redirectPath`)
  - Requires matching `MAGIC_LINK_SHARED_SECRET` and `CENTER_WEBSITE_BASE_URL` on
    `admin-portal-backend` and the builder
  - Do not re-introduce local auth UI in center-website (`/login`, `/register`, etc.)

## Database / Migrations Policy

- Shared business schema lives in AWS PostgreSQL RDS.
- `admin-portal-backend` uses the primary DB; `web-app-backend` uses the read replica.
- **All migrations** live in `admin-portal-backend/db/migrations/` only.
- No other repo owns shared schema migrations.

## Cross-Repo Impact Guide

| Change type | Repos to update |
|---|---|
| New DB column/table | `admin-portal-backend` (migration + admin API), then consumers |
| Staff UI for new field | `admin-portal` + `admin-portal-backend` |
| Public read of new field | `web-app-backend` (+ runtime **and** WP plugin if exposed publicly) |
| Center website section | `center-website` + `admin-portal-backend` + `web-app-backend`; align with WP plugin widgets where sections mirror each other; **Center Map** section also needs `threejs-map` |
| WordPress widget / Elementor feature | `wp-eyeonportal-plugin` + `web-app-backend` (+ admin-portal if staff configures it) |
| Magic link / Manage Website | `admin-portal` + `admin-portal-backend` + `center-website` |
| Kiosk display feature | `kiosk-electron` + `web-app-backend` (+ admin-portal if staff configures it) |
| Center map (floors, retailers, amenities, settings) | `threejs-map` + `admin-portal` + `admin-portal-backend` + `web-app-backend`; release bumps consumers (`center-website`, `center-website-runtime`, `kiosk-electron`, WP plugin via CI) |
| Map library UI/behavior change | `threejs-map` (publish npm) + bump `@eyeon/threejs-map` in admin-portal, center-website, kiosk-electron; runtime inherits center-website section dep; WP gets bundled assets on threejs-map release |
| API token scopes | `admin-portal` + `admin-portal-backend` + `web-app-backend` |
| EKS / deploy config | `eks_iac` + affected app repo |

## Center Map (`threejs-map`)

`threejs-map` is the shared React library (`@eyeon/threejs-map` on npm) that
powers interactive center maps across the platform.

### Data flow

1. **SVG floors** ‚Äî staff upload floor SVG files in admin-portal **Center Map**
   (`CENTER_MAP:FLOORS`). Stored in `mapit2_floors` (S3-backed `svg` key) via
   `admin-portal-backend` `/v1/mapit2/floors`.
2. **Map configuration** ‚Äî staff assign retailers, amenities, kiosks, routes,
   and map settings in admin-portal Center Map (`ROLE: PORTAL`). Writes go to
   `mapit2_data`, `mapit2_settings`, `mapit2_responsive`, etc. via
   `admin-portal-backend` `/v1/mapit2/*`.
3. **Public read** ‚Äî frontends fetch map data from `web-app-backend`
   `/v1/mapit2/data`, `/floors`, `/settings`, `/responsive` (API token).
4. **Render** ‚Äî `@eyeon/threejs-map` `MapBox` parses SVG layers, builds 3D
   geometry, and overlays retailer/amenity assignments.

### Consumers

| App | Role / mode | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `admin-portal` | `PORTAL` | Center Map module (`/center-map`) ‚Äî primary editor for floors + assignments |
| `center-website` | public section | `CenterMap` section (`src/public/sections/CenterMap`); builder preview proxies map API |
| `center-website-runtime` | public section | Same `CenterMap` section on published/test domains via shared `section-map` loaders |
| `kiosk-electron` | kiosk mode | Touch map + amenities; webpack aliases ESM build |
| `wp-eyeonportal-plugin` | `WP_SITE` | Elementor map widget; loads bundled `main.js` + `main.css` from `assets/map-releases/{version}/` |

### Release pipeline

On push to `threejs-map` `main` (version bump required):

1. Build library ‚Üí publish `@eyeon/threejs-map` to npm.
2. Build `threejs-wp/` wrapper ‚Üí copy `main.js`, `main.css`, source map to
   `wp-eyeonportal-plugin` repo at `assets/map-releases/{version}/`.
3. Commit to `mycenterportal/wp-eyeonportal-plugin` (`ThreeJS Map: {version} [skip ci]`).

Bump `@eyeon/threejs-map` in admin-portal, center-website, and kiosk-electron
when adopting a new library version. WP plugin picks up bundled assets
automatically from the CI push above.

## WordPress Plugin (`wp-eyeonportal-plugin`)

The WP plugin is an **ongoing first-class platform**, not a deprecated stack.

- Many centers keep WordPress because clients use it for non-EyeOn features.
- Plugin Elementor widgets and center-website sections may mirror the same
  center data ‚Äî keep public API contracts compatible for both.
- When building center-website sections (`section-registry.ts`, `src/public/`),
  treat matching Elementor widgets as a **parity reference** for UX, props, and
  data-fetch patterns ‚Äî do not import PHP into other repos.
- When changing public data used by widgets, update **both** the plugin and
  `web-app-backend` (and center-website-runtime if the same data is exposed there).

## Center Website (builder + runtime)

### Cross-repo rules

- Backend API changes ‚Üí `admin-portal-backend` (never business logic in builder/runtime).
- Published runtime contract changes ‚Üí `web-app-backend` must match what
  `center-website-runtime` reads.
- Manage Website / magic link / redirect changes ‚Üí `admin-portal` +
  `admin-portal-backend` + `center-website` together.

### Website lifecycle (1:1 with `centers`)

The `websites` table has `UNIQUE (center_id)` ‚Äî at most one website per center.

**Creation contract ‚Äî user consent required.** Website rows must only be created
via an explicit "Build Website" action, never on read or page-load flows.

| Endpoint | Behavior |
|---|---|
| `GET /v1/websites/by-center/:center_id` | Read-only; `404` if no website yet |
| `POST /v1/websites/by-center/:center_id` | Explicit init; idempotent; seeds defaults |

Builder proxies: `GET/POST /eyeon/api/v1/websites/by-center/:centerId`.

After Build Website, `seedWebsiteDefaults` (center-website) seeds via builder
write APIs: default page tree (Home + locked pages per module ‚Äî Stores, Dine,
Map, Deals, Events, News, Careers), default sections from `section-registry.ts`,
header/footer menus in `website_settings`, and a preview test subdomain
(`is_preview`). Banners global colors live in `web_slider_settings` (`center_id`)
via admin-portal, not `website_settings`. Re-invocations only fill empty slots;
user edits are never overwritten. `ensureForCenter` resolves `website_id` lazily
but does **not** seed.

**UI gate:** `center-website/src/components/builder/ProjectShell.tsx` ‚Äî on mount
read-only fetch; `404` shows "not initialized" + Build Website button (builder
children not mounted); Build Website POSTs then redirects to `/websites/:id/preview`.
"Manage Website" from admin-portal lands at `/websites/:id` (center ID).

### Deploy (eks-iac)

Manifests: `eks_iac/K8s/center-website-builder/` and `center-website-runtime/`.

| Tier | Builder host | Runtime test domains |
|---|---|---|
| Staging | `builder-staging.eyeonportal.com` | `{slug}-staging.eyeontest.com` |
| Production | `builder.eyeonportal.com` | `{slug}.eyeontest.com` |

- Runtime has no `DATABASE_URL`; bootstraps via `web-app-backend` `/v1/runtime/*`
  using `RUNTIME_SERVICE_SECRET`.
- `web-app-backend` staging needs `TEST_DOMAIN_SUFFIX=eyeontest.com`.
- Stored `website_domains.domain` prefix: `{slug}-staging` (staging) or `{slug}` (prod).
- **ALB gotcha:** while prod center-website is not deployed, prod ingress must not
  declare `*.eyeontest.com` or `builder.eyeonportal.com` ‚Äî a missing backend rule
  returns ALB 503 and blocks staging. See `eks_iac/K8s/ingress-rules/prod-alb/ingress.yaml`.
- Prod go-live: `eks_iac/docs/center-website-prod-go-live.md`.

